cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.CE 

This paper is about using evolutionary algorithms to train artificial neural networks, which falls under the category of neural networks and machine learning. Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the advantages of using evolutionary algorithms over conventional methods, which suggests that it could also be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the use of Chemical Reaction Optimization as a global optimization method could place it under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the application of this method to design and evolve neural networks could also place it under cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science).
